{"author":{"id":"2b947bb98f783c65c2f134ada93c677f0a535e8a2bac5748d2bac91c3620a963"},"ops":[{"type":6,"timestamp":1762439076,"nonce":"pUF9JCu+gZxb50rA/YOndLuTTwI=","metadata":{"github-id":"UCE_lAHOAW4Y0s7Uoe8nzpGrlsE"},"target":"1741642c0b733d8cc5209b2816e7ccabed64f583a754a24a5d82e7ba487349a6","message":"# Update mafGene tool to support local 2bit files\n\n## Description\n\nThe mafGene tool has been updated by Brian Raney to accept bigMaf files and local 2bit reference genome files instead of requiring database connections. We need to update the Galaxy wrapper to use this new functionality.\n\n## Background\n\nBrian Raney implemented changes in the UCSC Kent master branch (as of Oct 24, 2025) that eliminate the database dependency. This is a critical update that unblocks the mafGene wrapper completion.\n\n## Changes Made by UCSC\n\n- Tool now accepts bigMaf file instead of database parameter\n- New option added for specifying local 2bit file for reference genome\n- Removes MySQL connection requirement\n- Available in master branch of UCSC Kent tools\n\n## Tasks\n\n- [x] Build mafGene from UCSC Kent master branch\n- [ ] Update Galaxy wrapper to use bigMaf input instead of database\n- [ ] Add parameter for local 2bit reference file\n- [ ] Test with sacCer3 yeast dataset\n- [ ] Update tool documentation\n- [ ] Create example workflows\n\n## Resources\n\n- Documentation: https://genome.ucsc.edu/goldenpath/help/bigMaf.html\n- Test data: https://hgdownload.soe.ucsc.edu/goldenPath/sacCer3/multiz7way/maf/\n- Need to convert existing MAF to bigMaf format or download bigMaf from hgdownload\n\n## Related\n\n- Email thread with Brian Raney and Maximilian Haeussler (Oct 24-29, 2025)\n- Blocks completion of all four priority MAF tools\n- Related to Issue #2 (local file caching)","files":null}]}